# Commit identity

All commits in this repo must use:

- **Name:** David Su
- **Email:** dtscraft@gmail.com

## Required workflow

Do **not** run `git config user.email` or `git config user.name` (global or local).

When committing:

1. Stage files with `git add` as usual.
2. Commit via the wrapper:
   ```bash
   npm run git:commit -- -m "your message"
   ```
   Or with env vars:
   ```bash
   GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="David Su" GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="dtscraft@gmail.com" \
   GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="David Su" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="dtscraft@gmail.com" \
   git commit -m "your message"
   ```
3. Verify:
   ```bash
   git log -1 --format='%an <%ae> | committer: %cn <%ce>'
   ```

Multi-line messages:

```bash
npm run git:commit -- <<'EOF'
First line summary.

Optional body.
EOF
```
